## Risk register

- Snapshot CI guard may produce noisy diffs when unrelated code triggers a
  change in tool introspection (e.g. adding a new optional arg to a tool
  that gets signature-injected). Mitigation: the diff in the test failure
  output is the PR review artifact — reviewer sees what changed and updates
  the snapshot as part of the PR. This is the intended workflow, not noise.

- render_call_example() producing `<consumer_group>` placeholders might
  confuse the model into treating the placeholder as a literal string.
  Mitigation: the tests should assert that when the model sees the rendered
  prompt and is asked to call the tool, the actual call contains a real
  group name (not the literal `<consumer_group>`). If this fails in
  practice, switch placeholders to more clearly instructional strings like
  `"REPLACE_WITH_GROUP_NAME"` with a note in the prompt.

- Removing the outbound sanitizer is a soft API change. Any downstream
  consumer that depends on the sanitizer silently redacting UUIDs in
  responses will see them now. No known consumers in this project, but
  flag in CHANGELOG.


